![](images/javascript.png)

### 1. Optional Chaining `?.`

         .

```js
let user = undefined;
console.log(user.name); // Cannot read property 'name' of undefined 

user = null; 
console.log(user.name) // Cannot read property 'name' of null
```

 `user`          .

```js
console.log(user ? user.name : undefined);
```

ECMAScript2020 **Optional Chaining**    . 

   `null` `undefined`    `undefined` return             .

  1 2   .

```js
console.log(user?.name);
console.log((user !== undefined && user !== null) ? user.name : undefined);
```

 `const title = data?.article?.title`      .

### 2. Nullish coalescing Operator `??`

`||`     `true`         `false`    ,            . 

  .

```js
let result = data || 'default value';
console.log(result);
```

`data`    `result`  `data`  ,    `'default value'`  .

 `0`, `''`, `NaN`   falsy       `||`        . 

**Nullish coalescing Operator**    .

`??`      `null` `undefined`         return         .

  1 2   .

```js
console.log(data ?? 'default value');
console.log((data !== undefined && data !== null) ? data : 'default value');
```

### 3. globalThis

`globalThis` JavaScript       return.

 JavaScript    global    .

-   : window, self, frames 
-   : global 
- Web Worker : self 

            `globalThis`    .

```js
//    3 
console.log(globalThis);
console.log(window);
console.log(this);
```

### 4. Dynamic import

`import()`      .

`Promise`    `async/await` `then/catch`     .

```js
const myModule = './module.js';
import(myModule) 
	.then(module => { 
		module.default(); 
	})
	.catch(error => {
      // ... 
	});

// async/await 
(async () => {
	try {
		const module = await import('./module.js');
		const total = module.sum(1,1);
	} catch (error) {
		//... 
	} 
})();

```

